# Ghost — .cursorrules

## What this repo is
Ultra-low-latency Solana trading bot targeting pump.fun pool launches.
Written in Rust. NOT HFT generalist. NOT MEV bot in the broad sense.
Selective entry, deterministic exit, event-driven throughout.

## Hard architectural invariants — never violate these
- Yellowstone gRPC is the ONLY source of on-chain state. No new RPC calls.
- Dual-path submission: Jito bundle + Helius Sender. Never revert to single-path.
- Gatekeeper observes for 8-9s post pool creation, then emits verdict. No polling.
- Revolver reads shreds ~466ns hot-path latency. Nothing may block this path.
- DashMap<Pubkey, Instant> is the first-seen pool registry. No alternatives.

## Component map (read before touching anything)
ghost/
├── gatekeeper/     # Pool scoring: FTDI, DBIA, SFD, FSC, CPV, DES metrics
│                   # Config in TOML. dev_tx_ratio and dev_volume_ratio are primary discriminators.
├── revolver/       # Shred parser → shadow ledger → sell bundle pre-fire
│                   # Entry timing: -2.44ms relative to confirmed block
├── jito_client/    # Bundle builder, tip floor P75, BundleLandingStatus polling
├── helius/         # BUY fallback sender, dual-path routing
└── common/         # DashMap registry, shared types, timestamp utils

## Known active issues — do not re-solve without reading this
- BUY confirmation arriving 1-3s late vs 9s post-pool target
- Timestamp instrumentation needed at: Gatekeeper verdict / BUY submitted / BUY confirmed
- Jito bundles return `Invalid` consistently — Helius is primary BUY path for now

## Latency budget (hard numbers, not estimates)
- Shred hot-path: ~466ns (Revolver, same physical core via HT soft-borrow)
- Pool prediction from shreds: 23-25ms before CreatePool event
- Gatekeeper observation window: 8-9s from pool creation
- BUY target: within 9s of pool detection
- Entry timing vs confirmed block: -2.44ms

## Non-negotiable code rules
- No .unwrap() on fallible ops in hot paths
- No Vec/String allocation on hot paths — ArrayVec, SmallVec, &str
- All unsafe blocks: // SAFETY: comment mandatory
- Atomics: never default to SeqCst, use correct Ordering per pattern
- No lock held across .await — ArcSwap for read-heavy shared state
- thiserror for all domain errors. anyhow only in bin crates top-level.
- All RPC calls (the few that exist): explicit timeout set

## pump.fun specifics baked into this codebase
- Bot enters ALL pools (~8,670/day) — no pre-entry quality filter at CreatePool time
- Gatekeeper filters AFTER observation window, not before
- bonding_progress correlates mechanically with market_cap in losing pools — do not use as standalone signal
- dev_tx_ratio (d≈-0.88) and dev_volume_ratio (d≈-0.74) are most stable discriminators
- Six survivor metrics only: FTDI, DBIA, SFD, FSC, CPV, DES. 14 others were formally rejected.

## When writing code for this repo
1. Check if Yellowstone stream already exposes the data you need — it almost always does
2. Timestamp with Instant::now() at the three pipeline checkpoints above
3. If touching Revolver: do NOT add any allocation or blocking call, period
4. If touching Gatekeeper metrics: changes require re-calibration against TOML config
5. Prefer extending existing DashMap registry over introducing new shared state